# Kaven Frontend Rules (Brandbook v2.0.1 + Atomic Design)

## Stack
- Next.js App Router + React 19 + TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first)
- Design System source-of-truth: @kaven/ui

## Atomic Design
- atoms -> molecules -> organisms -> templates -> pages
- lower levels must not import higher levels

## Branding
- Primary: #10B981
- Secondary/Transform: #F97316
- Accent: #00D9FF
- Display font: Space Grotesk
- Body font: Inter
- Kai is technical adaptability symbol, never mystical mascot

## Component API
- Prefer standardized props: size, density, tone, variant, fullWidth
- Required size scale: 2xs, xs, sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl

## Accessibility
- icon-only buttons must have aria-label or sr-only text
- do not use focus:outline-none without focus-visible styles
- inputs require labels

## Tailwind
- forbid unresolved dynamic utility classes (e.g. shadow-${x})
- prefer cn() + cva() for variants
- avoid arbitrary values when token exists

## Performance
- avoid unnecessary use client
- use next/image where practical
- keep shared UI in @kaven/ui to reduce bundle drift
